          <Comment>For these reasons, this variant has been classified as Pathogenic. Loss-of-function variants in ATRX are known to be pathogenic (PMID: 18409179, 23681356). This variant has not been reported in the literature in individuals with ATRX-related conditions. This variant is an out-of-frame deletion of the genomic region encompassing exon(s) 8-9 of the ATRX gene. This is expected to create a premature translational stop signal and result in an absent or disrupted protein product.</Comment>
